description: Create a CiStatsReporter by inspecting the ENV for the necessary config

classes.label: CiStatsReporter
description: Object that helps report data to the ci-stats service

children.label: fromEnv
description: Create a CiStatsReporter by inspecting the ENV for the necessary config

children.label: isEnabled
description:
Determine if CI_STATS is explicitly disabled by the environment. To determine
if the CiStatsReporter has enough information in the environment to send metrics
for builds use #hasBuildConfig().

children.label: hasBuildConfig
description:
Determines if the CiStatsReporter is disabled by the environment, or properly
configured and able to send stats

children.label: timings
description:
Report timings data to the ci-stats service. If running in CI then the reporter
will include the buildId in the report with the access token, otherwise the timings
data will be recorded as anonymous timing data.

children.label: metrics
description:
Report metrics data to the ci-stats service. If running outside of CI this method
does nothing as metrics can only be reported when associated with a specific CI build.

children.label: reportTests
description: Send test reports to ci-stats

classes.label: ProcRunner
description:
Helper for starting and managing processes. In many ways it resembles the
 API from `grunt_run`, processes are named and can be started, waited for,
 backgrounded once they log something matching a RegExp...

children.label: run
description: Start a process, tracking it by `name`

children.label: stop
description: Stop a named proc

children.label: waitForAllToStop
description: Wait for all running processes to stop naturally

children.label: teardown
description:
Close the ProcRunner and stop all running
 processes with `signal`

children.label: getIndent
description: Get the current indentation level of the ToolingLog

children.label: indent
signature: { (delta: number): undefined; <T>(delta: number, block: () => Promise<T>): Promise<T>; <T>(delta: number, block: () => T): T; }

children.label: withType
description: Create a new ToolingLog which sets a different "type", allowing messages to be filtered out by "source"

children.label: type
description: A string that will be passed along with messages from this logger which can be used to filter messages with `ignoreSources`

children.label: write
description: Called by ToolingLog, extends messages with the source if message includes one.

children.label: level
signature: { name: "error" | "info" | "success" | "warning" | "debug" | "silent" | "verbose"; flags: { error: boolean; info: boolean; success: boolean; warning: boolean; debug: boolean; silent: boolean; verbose: boolean; }; }

children.label: write
signature: (writeTo: { write(msg: string): void; }, prefix: string, msg:

functions.label: diffStrings
description:
Produces a diff string which is nicely formatted to show the differences between two strings. This will
be a multi-line string so it's generally a good idea to include a `\n` before this first line of the diff
if you are concatenating it with another message.

functions.label: extract
description:
Extract tar and zip archives using a single function, supporting stripComponents
for both archive types, only tested with familiar archives we create so might not
support some weird exotic zip features we don't use in our own snapshot/build tooling

functions.label: getTimeReporter
signature: , group: string) => (startTime: number, id: string, meta: Record<string, any>) => Promise<void>

functions.label: observeLines
description:
Creates an Observable from a Readable Stream that:
  - splits data from `readable` into lines
  - completes when `readable` emits "end"
  - fails if `readable` emits "errors"

functions.label: observeReadable
description:
Produces an Observable from a ReadableSteam that:
  - completes on the first "end" event
  - fails on the first "error" event

functions.label: parseLogLevel
signature: (name: "error" | "info" | "success" | "warning" | "debug" | "silent" | "verbose") => { name: "error" | "info" | "success" | "warning" | "debug" | "silent" | "verbose"; flags: { error: boolean; info: boolean; success: boolean; warning: boolean; debug: boolean; silent: boolean; verbose: boolean; }; }

functions.label: pickLevelFromFlags
signature: (flags: Record<string, string | boolean | string[] | undefined>, options: { default?: "error" | "info" | "success" | "warning" | "debug" | "silent" | "verbose" | undefined; }) => "error" | "info" | "success" | "warning" | "debug" | "silent" | "verbose"

functions.label: transformFileStream
description:
Create a transform stream that processes Vinyl fs streams and
calls a function for each file, allowing the function to either
mutate the file, replace it with another file (return a new File
object), or drop it from the stream (return null)

functions.label: transformFileWithBabel
description:
Returns a promise that resolves when the file has been
mutated so the contents of the file are tranformed with
babel, include inline sourcemaps, and the filename has
been updated to use .js.

If the file was previously transformed with this function
the promise will just resolve immediately.

functions.label: withProcRunner
description:
Create a ProcRunner and pass it to an async function. When
 the async function finishes the ProcRunner is torn-down
 automatically

interfaces.label: CiStatsMetric
description: A ci-stats metric record

children.label: group
description: Top-level categorization for the metric, e.g. "page load bundle size"

children.label: id
description: Specific sub-set of the "group", e.g. "dashboard"

children.label: value
description: integer value recorded as the value of this metric

children.label: limit
description: optional limit which will generate an error on PRs when the metric exceeds the limit

children.label: limitConfigPath
description:
path, relative to the repo, where the config file contianing limits
is kept. Linked from PR comments instructing contributors how to fix
their PRs.

children.label: meta
description: Arbitrary key-value pairs which can be used for additional filtering/reporting

interfaces.label: CiStatsReportTestsOptions
description: Options for reporting tests to ci-stats

children.label: group
description: Information about the group of tests that were run

children.label: testRuns
description: Information about each test that ran, including failure information

children.label: startTime
description: ISO-8601 formatted datetime representing when the group of tests started running

children.label: durationMs
description: The number of miliseconds that the tests ran for

children.label: type
description: The type of tests run in this group, any value is valid but test groups are groupped by type in the UI so use something consistent

children.label: name
description: The name of this specific group (within the "type")

children.label: meta
description: Arbitrary metadata associated with this group. We currently look for a ciGroup metadata property for highlighting that when appropriate

children.label: startTime
description: ISO-8601 formatted datetime representing when the tests started running

children.label: durationMs
description: Duration of the tests in milliseconds

children.label: seq
description: A sequence number, this is used to order the tests in a specific test run

children.label: type
description: The type of this "test run", usually this is just "test" but when reporting issues in hooks it can be set to the type of hook
signature: "after all hook" | "after each hook" | "before all hook" | "before each hook" | "test"

children.label: result
description: "fail", "pass" or "skip", the result of the tests

children.label: suites
description: The list of suite names containing this test, the first being the outermost suite

children.label: name
description: The name of this specific test run

children.label: file
description: Relative path from the root of the repo contianing this test

children.label: error
description: Error message if the test failed

children.label: stdout
description: Debug output/stdout produced by the test

children.label: screenshots
description: Screenshots captured during the test run

interfaces.label: CiStatsTiming
description: A ci-stats timing event

children.label: group
description: Top-level categorization for the timing, e.g. "scripts/foo", process type, etc.

children.label: id
description: Specific timing (witin the "group" being tracked) e.g. "total"

children.label: ms
description: time in milliseconds which should be recorded

children.label: meta
description: hash of key-value pairs which will be stored with the timing for additional filtering and reporting

interfaces.label: Config
description:
Information about how CiStatsReporter should talk to the ci-stats service. Normally
it is read from a JSON environment variable using the `parseConfig()` function
exported by this module.

children.label: apiToken
description: ApiToken necessary for writing build data to ci-stats service

children.label: buildId
description:
uuid which should be obtained by first creating a build with the
ci-stats service and then passing it to all subsequent steps

interfaces.label: Message
description: The object shape passed to ToolingLog writers each time the log is used.

children.label: type
description: level/type of message

children.label: indent
description: indentation intended when message written to a text log

children.label: source
description: type of logger this message came from

children.label: args
description: args passed to the logging method

interfaces.label: MetricsOptions
description: Options for reporting metrics to ci-stats

children.label: defaultMeta
description: Default metadata to add to each metric

interfaces.label: TimingsOptions
description: Options for reporting timings to ci-stats

children.label: timings
description: list of timings to record

children.label: upstreamBranch
description: master, 7.x, etc, automatically detected from package.json if not specified

children.label: kibanaUuid
description: value of data/uuid, automatically loaded if not specified

children.label: type
description:
type name for this logger, will be assigned to the "source"
properties of messages produced by this logger

children.label: parent
description:
parent ToolingLog. When a ToolingLog has a parent they will both
share indent and writers state. Changing the indent width or
writers on either log will update the other too.

children.label: level
description: Log level, messages below this level will be ignored

children.label: ignoreSources
description:
List of message sources/ToolingLog types which will be ignored. Create
a logger with `ToolingLog#withType()` to create messages with a specific
source. Ignored messages will be dropped without writing.

children.label: writeTo
description:
Target which will receive formatted message lines, a common value for `writeTo`
is process.stdout

interfaces.label: Writer
description:
An object which received ToolingLog `Messages` and sends them to
some interface for collecting logs like stdio, or a file

children.label: write
description:
Called with every log message, should return true if the message
was written and false if it was ignored.

children.label: msg
description: The log message to write

misc.label: CiStatsTestType
signature: "after all hook" | "after each hook" | "before all hook" | "before each hook" | "test"

misc.label: CleanupTask
description:
A function which will be called when the CLI is torn-down which should
quickly cleanup whatever it needs.

misc.label: ParsedLogLevel
signature: { name: "error" | "info" | "success" | "warning" | "debug" | "silent" | "verbose"; flags: { error: boolean; info: boolean; success: boolean; warning: boolean; debug: boolean; silent: boolean; verbose: boolean; }; }
